<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-11-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Hovey</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-11-20"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 20, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your dispatch No. 156, of the 28th ultimo,
                            with the copy of the resolution of thanks of the congress of Peru and of
                            the correspondence touching the same, has been received.</p>
                        <p>It is gratifying to learn that the generous and spirited efforts of the
                            diplomatic and naval officers of the United States in that quarter,
                            towards the relief of the sufferings of Peruvian citizens from the
                            effects of the late terrible earthquakes, have been thus
                            acknowledged.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvin P. Hovey</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>